cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically sentence detection. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses transfer learning, a popular technique in AI, to improve the performance of the model. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a bidirectional GRU with self-attention as a baseline model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with extracting causal relations from texts, which is a task related to information retrieval. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for the task of causal sentence detection.
